{
  "texts": [
    "In general, most of the existing global pooling methods use one-step pooling operations, ignoring the rich hierarchical structure information inside the graph.",
    "To further improve the expressiveness of graph-level tasks, there is a need to develop novel pooling methods that can capture the hierarchical structure information of graphs.",
    "Such methods will be able to utilize the structural information of graphs more comprehensively and thus achieve better performance in various graph-level tasks.",
    "Compared with global pooling, hierarchical pooling completes the pooling operation by gradually constructing smaller-scale coarsened graphs.",
    "This strategy allows it to extract hierarchical structure information from the graph more effectively."
  ]
}